Sentencas: By modifying the proton conductor BaTbO3 with the element Co, it is discovered that the solubility of Co in BaTbO3 is restricted to 20 mol.%, and phase segregations happen for high Co doping concentrations in BaTbO3.
Titulo: Utilizing in-situ formed heterostructure oxides as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The fabrication of nominal BaTb0.5Co0.5O3 results in the in-situ development of the heterostructure cathode composed of BaTb0.8Co0.2O3+BaCoO3.
Titulo: Utilizing in-situ formed heterostructure oxides as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The critical role of the interface between BaTb0.8Co0.2O3 and BaCoO3 in enhancing fuel cell performance is to accelerate charge transfer kinetics, thereby enabling proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs) to operate at higher performance levels than cells employing BaTb0.8Co0.2O3 or BaCoO3 cathodes alone.
Titulo: Utilizing in-situ formed heterostructure oxides as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Furthermore, the favorable chemical stability of the BaTb0.8Co0.2O3+BaCoO3 nanocomposite is maintained, thereby enhancing the fuel cell's operational stability.
Titulo: Utilizing in-situ formed heterostructure oxides as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This research suggests that unanticipated phase segregation may occasionally improve the performance of the cathode, thereby presenting an interesting approach to cathode design in H-SOFCs.
Titulo: Utilizing in-situ formed heterostructure oxides as a cathode for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
